As an introverted, self-started creative individual who values privacy, running a business shouldn't feel so awkward, but sometimes it does. Most online resources and mentors tell you to engage with large (evil) tech companies in an extroverted way. Here, advertise, follow the algorithms, share your personal charm. Get verified on that platform, stay online 24/7, answer questions with your own videos, and respond immediately. Videos, videos, and videos again.
1/3
This year is a year of transformation for me.
I don't want to continue dedicating my money, data, and energy to large tech companies, nor do I want to listen to mentors who only push a single extroverted solution onto everyone. I'm exploring new business models while also striving to overcome my long-held belief that success can only be achieved by following a specific way of doing things.
Good luck to me!
The first step has been taken.
I left FB, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and deregistered my personal WhatsApp account.
Yesterday, I also removed the last external tracker—Google Analytics—from my website, and it felt great.
In order to better support GDPR, I recently subscribed to a European CRM service and will migrate my business to it over the next few weeks.
I transferred my MX records to Proton and now have full SPF, DKIM, and DMARC without having to pay Google for basic email verification.
3/3
