My situation is similar. I need to build a new website and am currently organizing my requirements for accessibility and privacy (so I won't use tools like Google Analytics), and I'm researching how to use Signal for video calls; this requires a lot of customer education! But I think it's worth it.
@user4 @user3 You're definitely capable of doing it! I'd be happy to share my experiences with you.
Website: You can check out @user5. It looks easy to use, has a nice interface, and is open source. I plan to migrate one of my websites there before my next renewal.
Signal: Check out cal.com. It's an open-source calendar service that integrates the ability to schedule video calls with platforms like Element and JITSI. It also supports Signal, but I haven't tested yet whether it only allows messaging or if it supports video calls.
I can recommend @user6. End-to-end encryption, decentralization, and open source.
